<div class="row"></div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-12">
      <div>
        <h5>What are levels?</h5>
        <p>If your students are working on the same activity, but at different levels, you may wish to have them record the level at which they are working. Some examples of these activities with levels include <a href="https://www.raz-kids.com/" target="_blank">Raz-kids</a> or <a href="https://www.ixl.com/">IXL</a></p>
        <p>Use this tab to list the levels that students can choose from when they track their data on this activity.</p>
      </div>
    <!-- <form ui-level-table-form> -->
      <input type="hidden" name="activity_id", value="<%= activity_id %>">
    	<table class="table">
    		<thead>
          <tr>
      			<th style="width:20%">Abbreviation<span style="vertical-align: super">^</span></th>
            <th style="width:60%">Name</th>
      			<th style="width:20%">
              <a href="#" ui-edit-button>Edit</a>
              <a href="#" ui-levels-done-button>Done</a>

            </th>
          </tr>
    		</thead>
    		<tbody ui-level-table-tbody>

    		</tbody>
    	</table>

      <table ui-hidden-table style="display:none">
        <tr ui-new-level-row> 
          <td> 
            <input type="text" name="activity_level[abbrevation]" class="form-control" id="newlevel" maxlength="2" ui-level-abbreviation-input>            
          </td>
          <td> 
            <input type="text" name="activity_level[name]" class="form-control" id="newlevel" ui-level-name-input>
          </td>
          <td><a href="#" class="btn btn-primary" ui-add-level-button>+</a></td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      <div>
        <span style="vertical-align: super">^</span>Abbreviation will show in your dashboard
      </div>

    <!-- </form> -->
  </div>
</div>